@startuml seq-21-admin-department-access-bulk
title PUT /admin/users/:userId/department-access — replace all

actor "Administrator" as A <<human>>
participant "Browser" as B <<browser>>
participant "Express\n/admin" as API <<service>>
database "PostgreSQL" as DB
participant "notifyManagerAssigned /\nnotifyMemberAdded" as N <<service>>

B -> API: PUT /admin/users/:userId/department-access\n{ assignments: [{ departmentId, accessLevel }] }

API -> DB: find user
API -> DB: $transaction:\n deleteMany UserDepartmentAccess\n createMany new rows
API -> DB: bumpAuthAfterDepartmentAccessChange\n(authVersion++ + sync refresh sessions)

loop rows with changed access vs oldMap
  API -> N: optional notification per row\n.fire-and-forget
end

API -> DB: findMany rows for response
API --> B: 200 [ access rows ]

note right of API
  Source: **apps/api/src/routes/admin.ts** (~2149+),\n**bumpAuthAfterDepartmentAccessChange**.
end note

@enduml
